# Deployed to CIRCE ~/.ignore by sync_configs.sh.
#
# Both fd and ripgrep honor .ignore files, so this controls what the Neovim
# file picker (snacks find-files) and live-grep walk. connect_nvim.sh drops you
# into $HOME, whose R library / tool dirs hold ~55k files on the slow network
# FS — scanning them made find-files hang ~10 s. Excluding them: ~10.6 s → 55 ms.
#
# Leading "/" anchors each pattern to the home root, so a project's own bin/ or
# R/ subdir under $HOME is NOT excluded — only the top-level tool dirs are.
/R/
/bin/
/quarto/
/texmf/
/h2o_jar/
/miniconda3/
/mambaforge/
/micromamba/
